<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imfillholes" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>imfillholes</refname><refpurpose>Fill holes in a binary image using an explicit name.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imfillholes(image)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Binary or numeric 2D image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Boolean image with holes filled.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imfillholes</function> is an explicit binary-only entry point that delegates to <function>imfill</function>.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[mask = zeros(7, 7) == 1; mask(2:6, 2:6) = %t; mask(4, 4) = %f; out = imfillholes(mask);]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imfill">imfill</link></member><member><link linkend="imfill">imfill</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Function introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
